.TH "__clocksource_register_scale" 9 "__clocksource_register_scale" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__clocksource_register_scale \- Used to install new clocksources
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __clocksource_register_scale
.BI "(struct clocksource *cs "  ","
.BI "u32 scale "  ","
.BI "u32 freq "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cs" 12
clocksource to be registered
.IP "scale" 12
Scale factor multiplied against freq to get clocksource hz
.IP "freq" 12
clocksource frequency (cycles per second) divided by scale
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns -EBUSY if registration fails, zero otherwise.

This *SHOULD NOT* be called directly! Please use the
\fBclocksource_register_hz\fP or clocksource_register_khz helper functions.
